    {
      "name": "tool-service-renegotiation (:8400, Python)",
      "description": "MCP server (streamable-http) exposing 7 governed tools to agent-runtime-renegotiation. Not a plain REST API - a real call needs an MCP client session (initialize, then tools/call over the MCP JSON-RPC framing), which Postman doesn't speak out of the box. The request below only confirms the server is up.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "MCP endpoint reachability check (GET)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{tool_service_url}}/mcp",
              "host": ["{{tool_service_url}}"],
              "path": ["mcp"]
            },
            "description": "Expect 406 Not Acceptable - that's the MCP server correctly rejecting a plain GET without the Accept/session headers an MCP client would send, which confirms it's listening. To exercise the actual tools (consultar_cliente, simular_proposta, etc.), use an MCP-aware client pointed at agent-runtime-renegotiation instead, or a proper MCP Inspector/client rather than Postman."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
